---------- Forwarded message ----------
From: Martin Edwards <martined@cogapp.com>
Date: 6 April 2011 11:00
Subject: Important: Torch Relay Map tweaks
To: Danny Sofer <danny@kitsite.com>
Cc: Claire Triggs <clairet@cogapp.com>, Lars Bortfeldt <lars@kitsite.com>


Hi Danny,
Can I ask for a couple of extra tweaks in the seadragon-init.js file?
I slightly zoomed out the map for zoom level 1, so now the scroll
wheel is not synced to zoom to the same level as the buttons.

Please could you make the following changes:
change:
Seadragon.Config.maxZoomPixelRatio = 1;
to:
Seadragon.Config.maxZoomPixelRatio = 0.991;

change:
Seadragon.Config.minZoomImageRatio = 0.76;
to:
Seadragon.Config.minZoomImageRatio = 0.787;

Also, the default animation speed is 1.5 seconds, which feels a bit
sluggish, I didn't realise we could change this, but have recently
found the property. Could we add a line to the bottom of the config
block (where the above code is), which is:
Seadragon.Config.animationTime = 1;


So the end results would be:
// Set initial state of map and effects of controls
Seadragon.Config.maxZoomPixelRatio = 0.991;
Seadragon.Config.autoHideControls = false;
Seadragon.Config.zoomPerClick = 1;
Seadragon.Config.zoomPerScroll = 10;
Seadragon.Config.zoomPerSecond = 10;
Seadragon.Config.minZoomImageRatio = 0.787;
Seadragon.Config.visibilityRatio = 1;
Seadragon.Config.animationTime = 1;
Thank you,
Martin Edwards /  Front End Web Developer

